Writer processor called HDFSWriterProcessor to write content directly&lt;br&gt;
into the Hadoop Distributed Filesystem. For those of you not familiar&lt;br&gt;
with Hadoop, it is an open source implementation of the Google File&lt;br&gt;
System and Map/Reduce system. It stores files by breaking them into&lt;br&gt;
chunks and distributing n replicas of each chunk across different&lt;br&gt;
nodes. It allows you to do high-speed distributed processing of your&lt;br&gt;
crawled data reliably, using a large cluster of machines.&lt;br&gt;
  &lt;br&gt;
The code is mostly isolated to new source files, but I had to make a&lt;br&gt;
couple of small changes to some of the existing interfaces. If there&lt;br&gt;
is any interest, I&#39;m willing to offer it to the project.&lt;br&gt;
